# Voice Cloning Audio Processing System - PRD

## 1. Overview

**Product**: Backend Voice Cloning Audio Processing System  
**Purpose**: Extract and process high-quality audio samples from video content for voice cloning services  
**Scope**: Admin-only backend tool for preparing audio samples  
**Timeline**: Phase 1 implementation  

## 2. Problem Statement

The expert clone platform needs to create voice clones of experts/speakers, but manually extracting and processing audio from videos is time-consuming and inconsistent. We need an automated system that can:
- Extract audio from various video sources (YouTube, uploaded files)
- Process audio to meet voice cloning service requirements
- Generate consistent, high-quality output suitable for services like Eleven Labs

## 3. Target Users

**Primary Users**: Platform administrators and content managers  
**Secondary Users**: Future integration with frontend user interface (Phase 2)  

## 4. Core Requirements

### 4.1 Input Sources
- **YouTube Videos**: Support YouTube URL processing (interviews, podcasts, lectures)
- **Video Files**: MP4, AVI, MOV, WebM formats
- **Audio Files**: MP3, WAV, M4A formats (direct processing)
- **Multi-Speaker Content**: Podcasts, interviews, panel discussions
- **Noisy Environments**: Background music, audience questions, ambient noise
- **Batch Processing**: Multiple files/URLs at once

### 4.2 Audio Processing Pipeline (Multi-Speaker & Noise Handling)
1. **Extraction**: Extract audio tracks from video files
2. **Content Analysis**: Identify content type (interview, podcast, lecture, solo speech)
3. **Speaker Diarization**: Map speaker segments and identify unique voices using AI clustering
4. **Speaker Analysis & Profiling**: Generate speaker statistics, quality scores, and audio samples
5. **Manual Speaker Selection**: User selects target speaker via CLI with preview samples
6. **Target Speaker Filtering**: Filter all processing to selected speaker segments only
7. **Noise Profiling**: Analyze background noise characteristics and music presence
8. **Music/Voice Separation**: Remove background music using AI separation models
9. **Multi-Speaker Filtering**: Remove segments with overlapping speech/interruptions
10. **Voice Activity Detection**: Isolate clean speech segments from target speaker
11. **Noise Reduction**: Remove ambient noise, audience sounds, microphone artifacts
12. **Speech Segmentation**: Identify continuous speech segments (avoid chopped sentences)
13. **Consistency Analysis**: Evaluate tone and performance consistency within speaker
14. **Normalization**: Target -23 to -18 dB RMS, -3 dB true peak
15. **Multi-Segment Selection**: Extract multiple diverse 60-second segments with highest speech quality and variety
16. **Final Quality Validation**: Ensure Eleven Labs compliance and speaker purity (>95% target speaker)

### 4.3 Output Requirements (Aligned with Eleven Labs Best Practices)
- **Duration**: 60 seconds (1 minute) per segment of clean speech
  - Minimum: 10 seconds (Eleven Labs requirement)
  - Target: 60 seconds per segment (optimal balance of quality and file size)
  - **Multiple Segments**: Generate 2-5 segments from longer content for improved voice modeling
  - **Rationale**: Eleven Labs supports multiple files (10MB each), enabling diverse voice samples
- **File Size**: Maximum 10MB per individual file (Eleven Labs hard limit)
  - 60 seconds WAV ≈ 5-6MB per file (safe under limit)
  - Multiple files allowed for richer voice training data
  - Prefer WAV format for maximum audio fidelity
- **Quality**: Minimum 22kHz sample rate, preferably 44.1kHz
- **Formats**: WAV (primary for quality), MP3 fallback only if needed
- **Bit Depth**: 16-bit minimum, 24-bit preferred
- **Volume Levels**: -23 dB to -18 dB RMS with true peak of -3 dB
- **Content**: Clear speech with no reverb, artifacts, background noise, or overlapping voices
- **Speaker Purity**: 95%+ single-speaker content (minimal cross-talk or interruptions)
- **Speaker Selection**: Manual selection from detected speakers with preview samples and statistics
- **Multi-Segment Selection**: Intelligent selection of multiple diverse 60-second portions from source material
  - **Diversity Priority**: Select segments with different speaking patterns, emotions, or content types
  - **Quality Ranking**: Order segments by quality score and audio characteristics
  - **Non-Overlapping**: Ensure segments don't overlap to maximize content diversity
  - **Minimum Spacing**: 30-second gap between selected segments to ensure variety

### 4.4 Service Compatibility
- **Eleven Labs**: Primary target service
- **Other Services**: Flexible output for future voice cloning providers
- **Metadata**: Generate compatibility reports for each service

## 5. Technical Requirements

### 5.1 Core Technologies
- **Language**: Python 3.9+
- **Audio Processing**: FFmpeg, pydub, librosa
- **Video Processing**: yt-dlp for YouTube, moviepy for general video
- **Speaker Diarization**: pyannote-audio, speechbrain
- **Noise Reduction**: noisereduce, spectral gating algorithms
- **Music Separation**: spleeter, demucs (AI-based source separation)
- **Voice Activity Detection**: webrtcvad, silero-vad
- **AI/ML**: Speech enhancement and separation models
- **Storage**: Local file system (Phase 1)

### 5.2 Performance Requirements
- **Processing Speed**: Handle 1-hour video within 10-15 minutes (includes AI processing)
- **Speaker Diarization**: Real-time or faster speaker identification
- **Music Separation**: 2-4x real-time processing for AI models
- **Concurrent Processing**: Support 2-3 simultaneous jobs (AI-intensive)
- **Memory Usage**: Efficient memory management for large files and AI models
- **File Size Limits**: Support videos up to 2GB

### 5.3 Quality Standards (Multi-Speaker Environment Optimized)
- **Speaker Identification**: Accurate speaker diarization (>95% accuracy)
- **Speaker Purity**: Target speaker content >95% of final output
- **Cross-talk Elimination**: Remove overlapping speech and interruptions
- **Music Contamination**: <5% music/background audio in final output
- **Noise Floor**: Background noise <-40dB relative to speech
- **Consistency Analysis**: Ensure consistent tone, performance, and audio quality throughout
- **Performance Preservation**: Maintain original speaking style (speed, emotion, inflection)
- **Voice Activity Detection**: Precise speech/non-speech boundary detection
- **Dynamic Range Control**: Avoid wide fluctuations in pitch and volume
- **Quality Scoring**: Rate output quality and purity (1-10 scale)
- **Error Handling**: Graceful failure with detailed error messages

## 6. System Architecture

### 6.1 Directory Structure
```
/app/voice-processing/
├── src/
│   ├── extractors/          # Video/audio extraction
│   ├── processors/          # Audio processing pipeline
│   ├── quality/             # Quality assessment
│   ├── utils/               # Shared utilities
│   └── cli/                 # Command-line interface
├── config/                  # Configuration files
├── output/
│   ├── raw/                 # Original extracted audio
│   ├── speakers/            # Speaker analysis results and samples
│   ├── diarization/         # Speaker identification results
│   ├── separated/           # Speaker-separated audio streams
│   ├── denoised/            # Noise-reduced audio
│   ├── segments/            # Clean speech segments
│   └── final/               # Ready for voice cloning
├── logs/                    # Processing logs
└── temp/                    # Temporary processing files
```

### 6.2 Processing Workflow
```
Input (Video/URL) → Validation → Audio Extraction → Content Analysis → 
Speaker Diarization → Speaker Analysis & Profiling → Manual Speaker Selection → 
Target Speaker Filtering → Music/Voice Separation → Noise Reduction → 
Voice Activity Detection → Speech Segmentation → Quality Analysis → 
Normalization → Multi-Segment Selection → Final Output
```

## 7. User Interface (CLI)

### 7.1 Basic Commands
```bash
# Speaker analysis and profiling (Step 1)
python voice-clone.py analyze-speakers video.mp4
python voice-clone.py analyze-speakers "https://youtube.com/watch?v=xyz"

# Single video processing with speaker selection (Step 2)
python voice-clone.py process video.mp4 --profile=elevenlabs --speaker=1

# YouTube URL processing with manual speaker selection
python voice-clone.py process "https://youtube.com/watch?v=xyz" --profile=elevenlabs --speaker=2

# Multiple segments with specific speaker
python voice-clone.py process-multiple video.mp4 --max-segments=3 --speaker=1

# Auto-select primary speaker (fallback)
python voice-clone.py process video.mp4 --profile=elevenlabs --speaker=auto

# Advanced processing with custom settings
python voice-clone.py process video.mp4 --profile=elevenlabs --speaker=1 --denoise=aggressive --music-separation=true
```

### 7.2 Configuration Profiles
- **elevenlabs**: Optimized for Eleven Labs requirements
- **generic**: General-purpose voice cloning output
- **custom**: User-defined parameters

## 8. Data Requirements

### 8.1 Input Metadata
- Source URL/file path
- Original duration and format
- Content description (optional)

### 8.2 Output Metadata
- Processing timestamp
- Quality metrics (SNR, speech ratio, etc.)
- Service compatibility scores
- File paths and formats generated
- Processing parameters used

### 8.3 Logging
- Processing status and progress
- Error logs with detailed stack traces
- Performance metrics (processing time, memory usage)
- Quality assessment results

## 9. Quality Assurance

### 9.1 Audio Quality Metrics (Multi-Speaker & Noise Handling)
- **Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR)**: Minimum 20dB
- **Volume Normalization**: Target -23 dB to -18 dB RMS, true peak -3 dB
- **Speaker Purity Score**: >95% target speaker content
- **Cross-talk Contamination**: <5% overlapping speech
- **Music Separation Quality**: <5% musical content in final output
- **Background Noise Level**: <-40dB relative to speech
- **Speech Clarity**: Detect mumbling, fast speech, inconsistent delivery
- **Voice Activity Precision**: Accurate speech/silence boundary detection
- **Consistency Score**: Measure tone and performance consistency throughout sample
- **Dynamic Range**: Control to prevent wide pitch/volume fluctuations
- **Speech-to-Total Ratio**: Maximize clean speech content, minimize silence/non-speech

### 9.2 Validation Checks (Eleven Labs Focused)
- **File format validation**: WAV preferred, MP3 128kbps+ as fallback
- **File size validation**: Maximum 10MB hard limit enforcement
- **Duration requirements**: 10 seconds minimum, 60 seconds maximum
- **Audio quality thresholds**: Volume levels, SNR, consistency scores
- **Content validation**: Speech-only content, no music/background noise
- **Performance consistency**: Flag samples with high variance in delivery
- **Segment selection quality**: Validate best 60-second portion selection
- **Service-specific requirement validation**: Eleven Labs compliance scoring

## 10. Error Handling

### 10.1 Common Error Scenarios
- Invalid YouTube URLs or restricted videos
- Corrupted or unsupported file formats
- Insufficient audio quality after processing
- No clear target speaker identified in multi-speaker content
- Excessive background music that cannot be separated
- High cross-talk ratio in interview/podcast content
- Network timeouts during downloads
- AI model loading failures (speaker diarization, music separation)
- Disk space limitations for temporary processing files

### 10.2 Recovery Mechanisms
- Retry logic for network failures
- Fallback quality settings
- Partial processing recovery
- Detailed error reporting for manual intervention

